    "Methodological issues, ranging from scientific misconduct to fraud, leading to reproducibility deficiencies, are serious problems that compromise the outcomes of clinical studies and undermine research quality [10].",
    "Furthermore, it is essential to recognize that failure to tackle such issues can lead to increased costs for the industry and make research processes more complicated [8].",
    "Therefore, it is crucial to fill these notable gaps in clinical research and address them in a broader literature context.",
    "Not only does it lead to more robust scientific findings, but it also fosters advancement within the healthcare domain.Based on all of these, alternative technologies and approaches are required to address complex clinical research requirements and improve clinical research practices [11].",
